reviewText: I love SEC Football and being from Louisiana, I always tell people that the SEC has the best football and basketball in the country.  Very good documentary.
Great quality DVD! Came super fast and was like new. Overall, great buy!

Not perfect, but good.  If you love the SEC I would certainly recommend it though.  Even if you a fan of just college football in general and of other conferences I still recommend it.  Love the parts on Neyland, Bryant, and the other legendary coaches of the SEC.
This is very a interesting DVD if you are a southern football fan. It isn't expensive and it has great footage.

The SEC is arguably the best conference for college football in the entire country. This video chronicles its history from the start in 1933. As a true college football enthusiast, I found this to be a great addition to my video library. History of SEC Football is a must for anyone who lives for Saturdays in the fall.

I enjoy watching SEC football every year.  This wasn't what I expected.  I am a die-hard Mississippi State fan and they didn't mention the Bulldogs.  They hardly mentioned the EGG Bowl.  I'm glad they mentioned Bear Bryant.  I despise Tennessee, Alabama, Auburn, LSU, Arkansas, and Ole Miss.  I especially hate Phil Fulmer.  GO MSU!!!
I bought this for my 8 year old and he (as well as the rest of us) have really enjoyed watching it.  It gives a good history of the overall SEC and each team including rivalries and traditions.
